    <fr:title text="Analytic convergence theorem">Analytic convergence theorem</fr:title>
    <fr:taxon>Theorem</fr:taxon>
    <fr:date>
      <fr:year>2025</fr:year>
      <fr:month>5</fr:month>
      <fr:day>25</fr:day>
    </fr:date>
    <fr:authors>
      <fr:author>Long Nguyen</fr:author>
    </fr:authors>
  </fr:frontmatter>
  <fr:mainmatter>
    <fr:p>Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[E]]></fr:tex> be open and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\{f_n\}]]></fr:tex> be a <fr:link type="local" href="sequence.xml" addr="sequence" title="Sequence">sequence</fr:link> of <fr:link type="local" href="holomorphic.xml" addr="holomorphic" title="Holomorphic">holomorphic</fr:link> functions on <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[E]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p>
    <fr:p>Suppose that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f_n \to  f]]></fr:tex> uniformly on <fr:link type="external" href="compact%20subsets">compact subsets</fr:link> of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[E]]></fr:tex>, then</fr:p>
    <fr:ul><fr:li><fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f]]></fr:tex> is also <fr:link type="local" href="holomorphic.xml" addr="holomorphic" title="Holomorphic">holomorphic</fr:link></fr:li>
<fr:li><fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\forall  k \in  \mathbb {N}]]></fr:tex>, the sequence of derivatives <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[f^{(k)}_n \to  f^{(k)} \quad  \text {uniformly}]]></fr:tex> on <fr:link type="external" href="compact">compact</fr:link> sets</fr:li></fr:ul>
    <fr:p>
      <fr:strong>Remarks</fr:strong>
    </fr:p>
    <fr:ul><fr:li>This result is specific to complex-valued functions</fr:li>
<fr:li><fr:link type="external" href="Uniform%20convergence">Uniform convergence</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\to ]]></fr:tex> the limit is <fr:link type="local" href="holomorphic.xml" addr="holomorphic" title="Holomorphic">holomorphic</fr:link></fr:li>
<fr:li>And also the convergence of any derivative of the sequence</fr:li></fr:ul>
  </fr:mainmatter>
